channeldata.description: The Object Oriented MicroMagnetic Framework (OOMMF) forms a completely functional micromagnetics package. OOMMF is written in C++. For portable user interfaces, it uses Tcl/Tk so that OOMMF operates across a wide range of Unix, Windows, and MacOSX platforms.  The recipe for building OOMMF conda package was developed by Martin Lang, Thomas Kluyver, Ryan A. Pepper, Marijan Beg, and Hans Fangohr at the University of Southampton, Max Planck Institute for the Structure and Dynamics of Matter, and Imperial College London as a part of OpenDreamKit – Horizon 2020 European Research Infrastructure project (676541) and EPSRC Programme Grant on Skyrmionics (EP/N032128/1).
